sentences: Maija Einfelde (born 2 January 1939) is a Latvian composer.

She continued her education at Alfrēds Kalniņš Music School in Cēsis, at Jāzeps Mediņš Music College in Riga, and then entered the Conservatoire of Latvia in 1966, studying composition with Jānis Ivanovs.
First Prize, Barlow Endowment for Music Competition, 1997
Grand Music Prize of Latvia, 1997
Award of the Ministry of Culture of the Republic of Latvia, 1999
